==English==
===Etymology===
Cf. F. affluent, L. affluens, -entis, p. pr.  See [[Affluence]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈæf.flu.ɛnt/

===Noun===
#A stream or river flowing into a larger river or into a lake; a tributary stream.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] //

===Adjective===
# Flowing to; flowing abundantly.
# Abundant; copious; plenteous; hence, wealthy; abounding in goods or riches.
# Being materially wealthy.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A body of water which receives waters from another. 
#:''The Mississippi River is an affluent of the Ohio River.''

